===Etymology===
{{bor|en|ota|حرم|tr=harem}} {{cog|tr|harem}}, from {{der|en|ar|حَرَم||something prohibited; sanctuary, women}}; and later also from {{m|ar|حَرِيم}} with same meaning, both from {{m|ar|حَرُمَ||be forbidden or unlawful}}. (Eng. usg. 1623)

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈhɑːriːm/|/(ˌ)hɑːˈriːm/|/ˈhɛərəm/|lang=en}}
* {{audio-pron|en-us-harem.ogg|ipa=/ˈhɛrəm/|lang=en|country=us}}
* {{a|US|CA}} {{IPA|/ˈhærəm/|/ˈhɛrəm/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[private]] part of an [[Arab]] [[household]], traditionally forbidden to [[male]] [[stranger]]s.
# A group of women, [[wife|wives]] and/or [[concubine]]s in a [[polygamous]] household.
# A group of female animals (cows) herded and controlled by a male animal (bull) of that species for breeding purposes. Such behaviour is exhibited by [[bovid]]s including cattle and buffalo as well as moose, elephants, seals, sea lions, and [[elephant seal]]s.
# {{lb|en|slang}} Any significant number of women together as a group; a [[bevy]].
# A [[genre]] of [[anime]] and [[manga]] in which a man is the [[love interest]] of three or more women.

